[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(49) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "But Aaron and his sons offered.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And Aaron and his sons were offering.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The participle denotes unintermitted action. “Aaron and his sons” is a technical name for the priests, to whom, according to this passage, three functions pertained: (1) sacrifice on the altars of burnt-offering and inconse; (2) the work of the most holy place (Holy of holies); (3) atonement for Israel by special rites of sacrifice and purification.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "According to all that Moses . . . commanded.—This refers to the entire ministry of the priests. The time in question is the Davidic age.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "According to all that Moses . . . commanded.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—This refers to the entire ministry of the priests. The time in question is the Davidic age.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The servant of God.—Comp. Deuteronomy 34:5; Joshua 1:1; Joshua 1:13. After his death, Moses is thrice called “servant of Jehovah,” in whose earthly household he had been faithful as a servant (Hebrews 3:5). He fore-figures in grand if imperfect outline that other servant of Jehovah, of whom the second half of Isaiah has so much discourse. “Servant of God” (Elohîm) the chronicler writes, because in his day the NAME was held in ever-increasing awe.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The servant of God.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 34:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 1:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 1:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". After his death, Moses is thrice called “servant of Jehovah,” in whose earthly household he had been faithful as a servant (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 3:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). He fore-figures in grand if imperfect outline that other servant of Jehovah, of whom the second half of Isaiah has so much discourse. “Servant of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "God” ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Elohîm",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") the chronicler writes, because in his day the NAME was held in ever-increasing awe.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 6:49",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 6:49",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But Aaron and his sons offered upon the altar — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The noblest part of the ministry was reserved for them. Aaron alone, and his successors in the high-priesthood, made atonement and ministered in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "most holy ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "place. But his sons, the other priests, offered on the altars of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "burnt- offering, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "incense.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
