    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 49-53.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - These verses allude to the more special functions of \"Aaron and his sons,\" as they are here called, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", his lineal descendants (vers. 4-15; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 7:2-5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), whose names, stopping at Ahimaaz, the eleventh generation, are the same with those of vers. 3-8. The manifest inference is that the present enumeration, stopping with the name of one contemporary with David (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 15:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), was borrowed from tables of the date of David, and not of the date of the Captivity (ver. 15). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
